abstract.text: The base class for acknowledged messages.

inlineContent.text: An acknowledged message is transmitted and acknowledged by each
receiving element by responding to that message. The response is
typically a status message. If a response is not received within
an arbitrary time period, the message will be retransmitted
Acknowledged messages are expected to be replied with a status message

abstract.text: The Config Low Power Node PollTimeout Get is an acknowledged message
used to get the current value of PollTimeout timer of the Low Power
node within a Friend Node.
The message is sent to a Friend Node that has claimed to be handling
messages by sending ACKs On Behalf Of (OBO) the indicated Low Power
Node. This message should only be sent to a Node that has the Friend
feature supported and enabled.
